The most timid of fire ant colonies. Quite amazing.
I work in pest control and it always bothers me when people whine about ants, spiders, or lizards.
Just thinking "But these are the main friends keeping the real nuisance pest out of your homes"
Short of wood damaging ants, they are relatively harmless until they start making dirt piles in your home like they are trying to move in.

snippet.textDisplay:
Answer to AC question of the week - dry and minimally decorated park is because:
1) To not give them any idea to move in
2) To avoid any parasites or poisonous stuff
3) Let all of us see what they are doing here
4) Easier to maintain
